#: ../../source/faq/index.rst:3
msgid "FAQ"
msgstr "Algengar spurningar"

#: ../../source/faq/index.rst:8
msgid "Why not just wrap at 80 columns?"
msgstr "Af hverju ekki bara að umbróta við 80 dálka?"

#: ../../source/faq/index.rst:10
msgid ""
"Column wrapping causes paragraph-wide reflows when you change a single "
"word. Reviewers see the entire paragraph in the diff, obscuring the "
"actual edit. Sentence-per-line formatting means a one-word change "
"produces a one-line diff."
msgstr ""
"Dálkaumbrot valda endurflæði á allri málsgreininni þegar eitt orð "
"breytist. Rýfjarar sjá alla málsgreinina í diff-inu, sem hylur "
"raunverulega breytinguna. Með einni setningu á línu gefur eins orðs "
"breyting eins línu diff."

#: ../../source/faq/index.rst:15
msgid "Does this affect how the document renders?"
msgstr "Hefur þetta áhrif á hvernig skjalið birtist?"

#: ../../source/faq/index.rst:17
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"No. LaTeX, Org-mode, Markdown, RST, and most prose formats treat single "
"newlines as whitespace. Two consecutive newlines start a new paragraph. "
"Snapper preserves paragraph breaks (blank lines) and only changes where "
"single newlines occur within a paragraph."
msgstr ""
"Nei. LaTeX, Org-mode, Markdown og flest textasnið meða einföldum "
"línuskiptum sem bil. Tvö línuskipti í röð byrja nýja málsgrein. Snapper "
"varðveitir málsgreinaskil (auðar línur) og breytir aðeins hvar einföldum "
"línuskiptum koma fyrir innan málsgreinar."

#: ../../source/faq/index.rst:22
msgid "My collaborators don't use snapper."
msgstr "Samstarfsfólk mitt notar ekki snapper."

#: ../../source/faq/index.rst:24
msgid "Will this cause problems?"
msgstr "Veldur þetta vandamáli?"

#: ../../source/faq/index.rst:26
msgid ""
"No. The formatting affects only whitespace within paragraphs. "
"Collaborators can edit normally and their changes will merge cleanly. For"
" fully transparent integration, use a git smudge/clean filter (see the "
"how-to guide)."
msgstr ""
"Nei. Sníðmótunin hefur aðeins áhrif á bil innan málsgreina. Samstarfsfólk"
" getur breytt eins og venjulega og breytingar þeirra sameinast hreint. "
"Notaðu git smudge/clean síu (sjá leiðbeiningar) til fullkomlega "
"gagnsærrar samþættingar."

#: ../../source/faq/index.rst:31
#, fuzzy
msgid "Why does snapper handle \"Dr. Smith\" correctly?"
msgstr "Af hverju klippir snapper \"Dr."

#: ../../source/faq/index.rst:33
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Snapper maintains curated abbreviation lists for English (80+), German, "
"French, Icelandic, and Polish. After Unicode sentence boundary detection,"
" it merges any splits that occurred at known abbreviation periods. Select"
" a language with ``--lang de`` (or set ``lang = \"de\"`` in "
"``.snapperrc.toml``). You can also add project-specific abbreviations via"
" ``extra_abbreviations`` in the config file."
msgstr ""
"Snapper hefur umsjónarskrá með 80+ skammstöfunum (titlar, latneskar "
"skammstafanir, fræðilegar tilvísanir, eins stafs upphafsstafir). Eftir "
"Unicode setningarmarkaskil sameinir það skiptingar sem voru við þekkt "
"skammstöfunarpunkta. Þú getur bætt við verkefnasértækum skammstöfunum í "
"gegnum ``.snapperrc.toml``."

#: ../../source/faq/index.rst:38
msgid "What about non-English text?"
msgstr "Hvað með texta á öðrum tungumáli en ensku?"

#: ../../source/faq/index.rst:40
msgid "Snapper supports non-English text in two ways:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq/index.rst:42
msgid ""
"**Rule-based abbreviation sets** for German (``de``), French (``fr``), "
"Icelandic (``is``), and Polish (``pl``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq/index.rst:44
msgid ""
"Select with ``--lang de``. The Unicode UAX #29 sentence boundary "
"algorithm works across all languages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq/index.rst:47
msgid ""
"**Neural sentence detection** via nnsplit for 9 languages (en, de, fr, "
"no, sv, zh, tr, ru, uk)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq/index.rst:49
msgid ""
"Enable with ``--neural --lang de``. Models download on first use (~4MB, "
"cached)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq/index.rst:52
msgid ""
"The rule-based approach handles most academic text well and runs 18x "
"faster. Use neural for languages where abbreviation rules fall short "
"(Chinese, Turkish, etc.)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq/index.rst:56
msgid "Can I use snapper as a library?"
msgstr "Get ég notað snapper sem forritasafn?"

#: ../../source/faq/index.rst:58
msgid ""
"Yes. The crate (``snapper-fmt``) exposes ``format_text()`` and all "
"internal modules:"
msgstr ""
"Já. Crate-ið (``snapper-fmt``) birtir ``format_text()`` og allar innri "
"einingar:"

#: ../../source/faq/index.rst:77
msgid "How fast is it?"
msgstr "Hversu hratt er það?"

#: ../../source/faq/index.rst:79
msgid ""
"Snapper processes typical academic papers (10-50 pages) in under 10ms "
"with the rule-based splitter. Neural mode adds ~200ms per file (model "
"load + inference via tract, pure Rust ONNX). No external runtime "
"dependencies."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq/index.rst:84
msgid "What about CRLF line endings?"
msgstr "Hvað með CRLF línuendingar?"

#: ../../source/faq/index.rst:86
msgid ""
"Snapper detects the input's line ending convention (LF or CRLF) and "
"preserves it in the output. Internally, processing normalizes to LF and "
"converts back before writing."
msgstr ""
"Snapper greinir línuendingarvenju inntaksins (LF eða CRLF) og varðveitir "
"hana í úttaki. Innbyrðis staðlar vinnslan á LF og umbreytir aftur áður en"
" skrifað er."

#: ../../source/faq/index.rst:90
msgid "Can I skip formatting for specific sections?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq/index.rst:92
msgid "Yes. Use ``snapper:off`` and ``snapper:on`` pragmas in comments:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq/index.rst:95
msgid "Org: ``# snapper:off`` / ``# snapper:on``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq/index.rst:97
#, python-format
msgid "LaTeX: ``% snapper:off`` / ``% snapper:on``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq/index.rst:99
msgid "Markdown: ``<!-- snapper:off -->`` / ``<!-- snapper:on -->``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq/index.rst:101
msgid "RST/Plaintext: ``snapper:off`` / ``snapper:on`` on their own line"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq/index.rst:103
msgid ""
"Text between these markers passes through unchanged. Useful for poetry, "
"aligned text, or ASCII art."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq/index.rst:107
#, fuzzy
msgid "What formats does snapper support?"
msgstr "Af hverju klippir snapper \"Dr."

#: ../../source/faq/index.rst:109
msgid ""
"Org-mode, LaTeX, Markdown, reStructuredText, and plaintext. Format auto-"
"detects from the file extension. Override with ``--format rst`` (or "
"``org``, ``latex``, ``markdown``, ``plaintext``)."
msgstr ""

